    • Enum Constant Detail

      • INITIALIZATION

        public static final Runlevel INITIALIZATION
        Indicates the application has not done anything. Variable initialization has only occurred.

      • STARTUP

        public static final Runlevel STARTUP
        Indicates the application has started all managers and dispatchers then loads plugins.

      • MAINLOOP

        public static final Runlevel MAINLOOP
        Indicates the application has started the main loop. Expect heartbeat and task execution.

      • NETWORKING

        public static final Runlevel NETWORKING
        Indicates the application has started the networking (UDP in particular) and is waiting on the cluster.

      • STARTED

        public static final Runlevel STARTED
        Indicates the application has started.

      • RELOAD

        public static final Runlevel RELOAD
        Indicates the application is reloading. TODO Not Implemented - Needs to disconnect from cluster, unload managers and dispatchers, then reload everything.

      • SHUTDOWN

        public static final Runlevel SHUTDOWN
        Indicates the application is preparing to shutdown. Best point to get the most critical shutdown logic done before managers, dispatchers, and plugins are disposed of.

      • DISPOSED

        public static final Runlevel DISPOSED
        Indicates the application has been shutdown. The main loop will cease execution here. It's like no plugins will ever see this Runlevel as they have been unloaded.

      • CRASHED

        public static final Runlevel CRASHED
        Indicates the application has CRASHED. Similar to DISPOSED with the exception that Plugins might see this one depending on the exception source. A crash report will soon be generated and dispatched to the server admin.
